    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-09T13:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="449"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6250</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1917-08-09T13:50:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1917-08-08T00:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 9, 1917, 1.50
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Peruvian Senate last night unanimously adopted following resolution: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>In view of the high and democratic ideas expressed by President <persName
                                corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName> on the Republic of the United
                            States taking part in the European conflict, the Senate of Peru declares
                            that it emits a vote of sympathy to the United States of North America
                            on account of the declarations made by its President that embody for the
                            republics of the American Continent the rules of the united action to
                            which their purposes must be consecrated.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
